Now, I'ma say
four things to you,

32:36.476 --> 32:37.868
and I need you
to repeat them back to me

32:37.912 --> 32:39.696
in the order
that I say them, okay?

32:39.740 --> 32:40.915
- Whatever.
- All right.

32:40.959 --> 32:43.396
Cow, pig, duck, horse.

32:47.574 --> 32:48.792
Cow.

32:48.836 --> 32:49.793
Pig.

32:49.837 --> 32:50.794
Duck.

32:50.838 --> 32:52.187
Horse.

32:54.233 --> 32:57.236
Horse.
Pig, duck, cow.

32:57.279 --> 32:58.672
All right.

32:58.715 --> 33:00.587
Now, with your good hand,

33:00.630 --> 33:03.764
I need you to touch
your nose, ear, and chin.

33:03.807 --> 33:04.983
Come on, man, what was that?

33:05.026 --> 33:07.986
Nose, ear, chin.

33:14.688 --> 33:17.125
<i>[apprehensive music]</i>

33:17.169 --> 33:19.606
All right,
let's get you processed.

33:19.649 --> 33:20.999
Hurry up.

33:26.352 --> 33:28.571
Okay, all bile ducts
reattached.

33:28.615 --> 33:29.964
Finished up the hepatic artery.

33:30.008 --> 33:31.531
Removing clamps.

33:31.574 --> 33:33.402
<i>[tense music]</i>

33:33.446 --> 33:36.275
Yeah, not hearing
any systemic circulation.

33:36.318 --> 33:38.277
Yeah, liver's
not pinking up either.

33:38.320 --> 33:40.279
Looks like hepatic artery
thrombosis.

33:40.322 --> 33:41.758
We're gonna need
to remove that clot.

33:41.802 --> 33:43.195
Get me a small Fogarty balloon

33:43.238 --> 33:45.327
and 500 units of heparin,
Betty.

33:45.371 --> 33:47.808
Reopening the hepatic
arterial anastomosis.

33:47.851 --> 33:50.637
Sats down to 91.

33:50.680 --> 33:51.942
Inflate.

33:51.986 --> 33:53.727
The balloon's too small.

33:53.770 --> 33:54.989
Next size catheter, right?

33:55.033 --> 33:56.469
The patient's
not even a year old.

33:56.512 --> 33:58.471
Any wider and we risk
perforating the vessel.

33:58.514 --> 34:01.126
Well, I don't see
as we have any other choice.

34:01.169 --> 34:02.779
Reset. One size up.

34:02.823 --> 34:09.177
<i>â™ª</i>

34:10.352 --> 34:12.311
Oh, this one feels too tight.

34:12.354 --> 34:13.660
I do not want
to rupture this artery.

34:13.703 --> 34:15.009
[monitor beeping]

34:15.053 --> 34:16.271
Sats are still lowering.

34:16.315 --> 34:18.186
86. 84.

34:18.230 --> 34:20.101
We might have to go back
to the smaller catheter.

34:20.145 --> 34:21.885
Why don't you let me try?

34:21.929 --> 34:23.539
I might have a better angle.

34:23.583 --> 34:24.801
Here.

34:24.845 --> 34:31.199
<i>â™ª</i>

34:31.243 --> 34:33.201
Crockett.
- Give me a sec.

34:37.727 --> 34:39.207
Now.

34:41.644 --> 34:43.646
Here's the clot.

34:43.690 --> 34:46.867
Sats climbing.
88, 93.

34:46.910 --> 34:48.869
96 and holding.

34:48.912 --> 34:50.218
Moment of truth.

34:55.484 --> 34:58.966
Yeah.
Looks like an adequate flow.

34:59.009 --> 35:00.446
[sighs]

35:02.100 --> 35:03.753
A quick turnaround, Ellis.

35:03.797 --> 35:04.928
I'm impressed.

35:04.972 --> 35:06.495
Quality medical care.

35:07.714 --> 35:09.498
I'm gonna send over
an endocrinologist,

35:09.542 --> 35:11.544
make sure this doesn't
happen again.

35:11.587 --> 35:12.719
Thank you, Doc.

35:12.762 --> 35:14.068
Hey, take care.

35:14.112 --> 35:17.071
<i>[soft music]</i>

35:17.115 --> 35:18.159
<i>â™ª</i>

35:18.203 --> 35:20.640
You gonna be okay?

35:20.683 --> 35:22.120
I should be asking you that.

35:25.123 --> 35:27.908
Nice meeting you,
Nurse Lockwood.

35:27.951 --> 35:29.997
You too.

35:30.040 --> 35:31.999
both: Bye.

35:39.180 --> 35:40.834
Can I give you a kiss?

35:40.877 --> 35:42.749
[chuckles]
Sure.

35:42.792 --> 35:49.973
<i>â™ª</i>

35:57.459 --> 35:58.417
Here.

36:00.158 --> 36:04.162
So you asked what was going on.

36:04.205 --> 36:06.164
I had a biopsy.

36:06.207 --> 36:07.513
Oh, Maggie.

36:07.556 --> 36:10.255
No, no, no, no.
It's benign.

36:10.298 --> 36:13.127
I'm okay.
- That's great news.

36:13.171 --> 36:14.346
Yeah, it is.

36:15.695 --> 36:18.785
Well, long as
we're coming clean,

36:18.828 --> 36:20.265
I wish Stevie was staying.

36:22.310 --> 36:25.139
But like Ellis says,

36:25.183 --> 36:26.793
life can throw you a curveball.

36:26.836 --> 36:32.277
<i>â™ª</i>

36:32.320 --> 36:34.540
Terrell, honey,
let him speak.

36:34.583 --> 36:36.106
It's important.

36:36.150 --> 36:38.239
You need to be tested
by a specialist,

36:38.283 --> 36:39.632
but I believe you have

36:39.675 --> 36:42.417
a neurological condition
called dyslexia.

36:42.461 --> 36:45.246
Something you were born with.
- Dyslexia?

36:45.290 --> 36:47.640
It affects how the brain
processes information.

36:47.683 --> 36:49.119
You know how you've
always had trouble

36:49.163 --> 36:51.905
with left and right,
and how you mix up words.

36:51.948 --> 36:54.212
Everybody does that.

36:54.255 --> 36:55.517
It's, uh...

36:57.345 --> 36:58.738
It's why you never learned
to read.

36:58.781 --> 37:00.435
- Dude, who says I can't read?
- Terrell, come on.

37:00.479 --> 37:01.828
Listen, it's not your fault.

37:01.871 --> 37:03.830
And it doesn't mean
that you're not smart.

37:03.873 --> 37:06.006
No, no. Not at all.

37:06.049 --> 37:07.486
It's a learning disability.

37:07.529 --> 37:11.316
It has nothing to do
with intelligence.

37:11.359 --> 37:13.187
You should have been
diagnosed as a kid

37:13.231 --> 37:15.233
and helped,
but, psh, let's face it,

37:15.276 --> 37:16.712
our school?

37:16.756 --> 37:18.671
They didn't have the funding
for that kind of thing.

37:20.977 --> 37:22.022
I thought I was stupid.

37:22.065 --> 37:24.851
No. No, baby. No.

37:24.894 --> 37:27.549
It's not too late
to change things, bro.

37:29.464 --> 37:31.640
Dyslexia is not
all that uncommon,

37:31.684 --> 37:33.860
and there's plenty
that can be done for you.

37:33.903 --> 37:41.084
<i>â™ª</i>

37:53.749 --> 37:56.274
His life could have been
so different if he'd known.

38:03.281 --> 38:05.805
That was great work today,
Dr. Marcel.

38:05.848 --> 38:07.546
Thank you. You too.

38:09.417 --> 38:12.377
- Okay, well, good night.
- Good night.

38:12.420 --> 38:15.510
Oh, God, Crockett...

38:18.252 --> 38:19.645
It's better this way.

38:21.168 --> 38:22.430
Is it?

38:26.782 --> 38:29.176
Not the way I see it.

38:29.219 --> 38:36.314
<i>â™ª</i>

38:43.625 --> 38:44.887
- Dan--
